node.text:
First light on Mount Taranaki 🏔 always a sucker for a mountain reflection combo and this place never disappoints. I’ve had every sort of condition here but no matter what nature presents me it always looks so beautiful.

Isn’t Mount Taranaki just the perfect mountain ?!

node.text:
Some of my favourite photos I’ve ever taken have been from locations that are a little harder to get to with some hiking involved. The reward always feels better when a bit of effort has been put in and it’s so good to get out in nature and burn off some energy! 

I’ve got a new post up on my blog with the top 5 South Island day hikes which I think are the best for photography! 

Check out the link in my bio for more or my story highlight. 

There’s also a Top 5 North Island Day Hikes blog so you can get your full NZ hiking fix and start planning the next adventure 👣

There’s always a light at the end of the tunnel ..

Or in this case .. a magical beach. Exploring new and epic places along the coast with @iamtheflyingkiwi .. NZ never ceases to blow me away. As much as I love to run away to the mountains , the sea will always have my soul.

Hope everyone had a great weekend 🌊

node.text:
Strolling across Mars at sunset .. except Mars was an epic landscape in @northlandnz New Zealand that really doesn’t get enough attention!

After a lifetime (well .. my lifetime) of wanting to visit the Te Paki sand dunes, I finally made it and it was just as beautiful as I had imagined it would be.

Some of the dunes can reach up to 100 metres from over 1 million years of volcanic sand build up. 

@iamtheflyingkiwi and I set off on an amazing (and hectic) road trip last week that saw us cover a record amount of driving to get to the top of New Zealand in the shortest space of time .. we are crazy 😝 but it was so worth it. 

I totally recommend taking the trip up here .. check out my story highlight for more.

Unfortunately the Instagram crop didn’t help me much with the second shot as it was composed as a landscape. 

Have a great weekend everyone ✌️

node.text:
A little set of my favourites featuring Spring, Winter, Autumn and Summer. What’s your favourite season? 💙

Here in New Zealand we are still waiting for winter to arrive in its entirety … each year it feels like summer is a little bit longer and winter is little bit shorter .. a sure sign Mother Earth is changing. 

To be honest I just feel lucky to be able to experience them all in this pretty little country I get to call home. In saying that, I look forward to the day when we can travel again and experience the seasons all over the world 🌎 

Have a great weekend everyone!

node.text:
#ad Who else loves experiencing the snow and mountains during winter? 
 
One of my favourite places to visit when the cooler temperatures hit New Zealand is Aoraki Mount Cook National Park. There are hiking options here that you can still experience even in the thick of winter. The Hooker Valley Track and Tasman Lake hike are two of the tracks that not only offer incredible views, they are fun to walk and look so magical with some snow!
 
I am super stoked to be partnering with @mountainwarehouse to showcase some of their waterproof hiking gear that I wore recently while in Aoraki Mountain National Park. In these shots I am wearing the Rainforest Waterproof Jacket, the Explorer Womens Zip off Trousers and Glacier Waterproof Ultra Grip Boots. They were all ultra comfortable to hike in and kept me warm and dry the entire time!
 
For a limited time you can get 15% off Mountain Warehouse gear by using the code RACH15 at the check out, I highly recommend you check out their range of gear! Link in my story and highlights
